<div class="container pull-center">
  <h1>About Blocmetrics</h1>
  <p>BlocMetrics is an API tracking and reporting application that lets you track the traffic to your registered web application. </p>
  <ol>
    <li><%= link_to "Sign up", new_user_registration_path %> for an account </li>
    <li><%= link_to "Register Here", new_registered_application_path %> -- the name and URL of your web application</li>
    <li>Add the following snippet to your application's code with your own <span class='highlight'>"Event Name"</span>:</li>
  </ol>

  <div class='snippet'>
    <p>
      var blocmetrics = {};<br/>
      blocmetrics.report = function(eventName){
        <div class="code-inside">
          var event = { event: { name: eventName } };</br>
          var request = new XMLHttpRequest();</br>
          request.open("POST", "https://salty-citadel-61389.herokuapp.com/api/events", true);</br>
          request.setRequestHeader('Content-Type', 'application/json');</br>
          request.send(JSON.stringify(event));</br>
        </div>
      }</br>
      </br>
      blocmetrics.report(<span class="highlight">"Event Name"</span>);</br>
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>Please feel free to register many URL's from your site as you wish, and add this snippet to each favorite page to track your app.</P>
  <h6 class = 'pull-right'>Made by Jane with love</h6>
</div>
